> @exceptionfactory Are the locales where these CI builds English speaking?

@dan-s1, no the automated builds use different locales (`EN`, `HI`, `JP`, and `FR`) to surface potential issues.

It sounds like changing the tests to avoid using language-based indicators (such as AM and PM) would be the best way forward.

Since maven repository has only jjwt 0.9.1 https://mvnrepository.com/artifact/io.jsonwebtoken/jjwt , I have upgraded to that only.
The 0.11.5 mentioned in JIRA NIFI-11467 is for the jjwt-api https://mvnrepository.com/artifact/io.jsonwebtoken/jjwt-api.

@exceptionfactory Could you please review it.
